== 糖與健康 (建議食用量) ==
除了肥胖及糖尿病風險外，由於糖在體內會轉換為[[血脂|血脂]](脂肪)，吃糖過量也會造成高血脂及脂肪肝。

美國認為糖的安全食用量是低於總熱量的10%，而[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]（[[WHO|WHO]]）則認為要低於5%；無論是哪種標準，都是很容易過量的標準。

2015年3月4日，[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]（WHO）公布新版飲食指南，建議將游離糖的量減至每日攝取總熱量的5%以下，亦即不超過25[[公克|公克]]（6[[茶匙|茶匙]]），以避免[[肥胖症|肥胖症]]、[[蛀牙|蛀牙]]和[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]、[[心血管疾病|心血管疾病]]甚至癌症等文明病。<ref name="WHO 2015"/><ref>{{cite news |url= http://udn.com/news/story/7266/746982 |title= 遠離肥胖 每日糖分不超過25克 |date= 2015-03-06 |newspaper= [[聯合報|聯合報]] |author= 陳韻涵 |accessdate= 2015-06-10 |archive-date= 2021-04-19 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210419231326/https://udn.com/news/story/7266/746982 |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=  |title= 世衛組織：成人每天吃糖不應超過25克 | date=2015-03-05| publisher= 日本經濟新聞社|work= [[日本經濟新聞|日本經濟新聞]]|author=原克彥|location=[[日內瓦|日內瓦]]}}[http://zh.cn.nikkei.com/politicsaeconomy/politicsasociety/13393-20150305.html {{Wayback|url=http://zh.cn.nikkei.com/politicsaeconomy/politicsasociety/13393-20150305.html |date=20210313181429 }} {{zh-hant}}]、[http://cn.nikkei.com/politicsaeconomy/politicsasociety/13393-20150305.html {{Wayback|url=http://cn.nikkei.com/politicsaeconomy/politicsasociety/13393-20150305.html |date=20210419231353 }} {{zh-cn}}]</ref>

[https://hms.harvard.edu/ 哈佛醫學院] {{Wayback|url=https://hms.harvard.edu/ |date=20210527151856 }}亦發表了健康飲食餐盤指引, 當中明確表示, 應避免含糖之飲料, 限制糖的攝取。因為糖為熱量的主要來源, 而且通常營養價值很低。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hsph.harvard.edu/nutritionsource/healthy-eating-plate/|title=Healthy Eating Plate & Healthy Eating Pyramid|accessdate=|author=Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health|date=|publisher=Harvard Medical School|archive-date=2021-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210525023842/https://www.hsph.harvard.edu/nutritionsource/healthy-eating-plate/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

游離糖分包括食物及飲料中由製造商、廚師或是消費者加入的單糖及雙糖，以及蜂蜜、糖漿、果糖及濃縮果汁中的天然糖分<ref name="WHO 2015">See [http://www.who.int/nutrition/publications/guidelines/sugars_intake/en/ ''Guideline: Sugars intake for adults and children. Geneva: World Health Organization; 2015'' ] {{Wayback|url=http://www.who.int/nutrition/publications/guidelines/sugars_intake/en/ |date=20150817100425 }}</ref>。

== 治疗性 ==
{{Fact|由于吃糖是跳过了绝大部分复杂的咀嚼切碎研磨食物并将其化学消化的过程，改而直接吸营养的更有效摄入方式，在日常生活中具有广泛的应用：生长期儿童需要经常吃糖保证一定食欲；因饮食不规律而长期饥饿导致消化道溃疡症的消瘦患者需要在手边准备糖，时刻补充血糖营养，防止低血糖病发；医院配置点滴溶液时常使用葡萄糖溶液作为母液……|time=2017-08-05T03:56:00+00:00}}

== 成癮性 ==
<!--{{main|Sugar addiction}}-->
糖類成癮是指糖和許多{{le|食物成癮|food addiction}}症狀（如{{le|暴飲暴食|Binge eating}}、戒斷、食物渴求及[[交叉致敏|交叉致敏]]）之間的關係。有些科學家聲稱過量的糖類或[[糖果|糖果]]攝取會出現類似{{le|阿片類使用疾患|Opioid use disorde|類似海洛英中毒}}的症狀<ref name="Nestler">{{cite journal | author = Robison AJ, Nestler EJ | title = Transcriptional and epigenetic mechanisms of addiction | journal = Nat. Rev. Neurosci. | volume = 12 | issue = 11 | pages = 623–637 |date=November 2011  | pmid = 21989194 | pmc = 3272277 | doi = 10.1038/nrn3111 | quote = ΔFosB has been linked directly to several addiction-related behaviors ...  Importantly, genetic or viral overexpression of ΔJunD, a dominant negative mutant of JunD which antagonizes ΔFosB- and other AP-1-mediated transcriptional activity, in the NAc or OFC blocks these key effects of drug exposure14,22–24. This indicates that ΔFosB is both necessary and sufficient for many of the changes wrought in the brain by chronic drug exposure. ΔFosB is also induced in D1-type NAc MSNs by chronic consumption of several natural rewards, including sucrose, high fat food, sex, wheel running, where it promotes that consumption14,26–30. This implicates ΔFosB in the regulation of natural rewards under normal conditions and perhaps during pathological addictive-like states. }}</ref><ref name="Natural and drug addictions">{{cite journal | author = Olsen CM | title = Natural rewards, neuroplasticity, and non-drug addictions | journal = Neuropharmacology | volume = 61 | issue = 7 | pages = 1109–22 |date=December 2011  | pmid = 21459101 | pmc = 3139704 | doi = 10.1016/j.neuropharm.2011.03.010 | url = }}</ref><ref name="Avena-Rada-Hoebel">{{cite journal | last1 = Avena | first1 = Nicole M. | last2 = Rada | first2 = Pedro | last3 = Hoebel | first3 = Bartley G. | year = 2008 | title = Evidence for sugar addiction: Behavioral and neurochemical effects of intermittent, excessive sugar intake | journal = Neuroscience & Biobehavioral Reviews | volume = 32 | issue = 1| pages = 20–39 | pmc=2235907 | pmid=17617461 | doi=10.1016/j.neubiorev.2007.04.019}}</ref>，日本白澤卓二稱為「糖中毒」<ref>{{cite book|date=2014-05-07|origyear=2014|author2=楊詠婷（譯者）|title= 《2週間で効果がでる白澤式ケトン食事法》|trans-title=《糖中毒，當然會三高！》| author=白澤卓二|publisher=方舟文化|pages= 192頁|isbn=978-9869058605}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.businesstoday.com.tw/article-content-80731-109527 |title= 你以為只有毒品會慢慢上癮嗎? |date= 2014-08-01 |publisher= 今周刊 |access-date= 2016-05-19 |archive-date= 2020-11-01 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201101102821/http://www.businesstoday.com.tw/article-content-80731-109527 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

